{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_47","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job for `com.oracle.database.jdbc:ojdbc11:23.8.0.25.04` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4502-library-new-request-com.oracle.database.jdbc-ojdbc11-23.8.0.25.04-6c861285\n\nThe most likely failing stage is final `nativeTest` verification, not the active coverage target itself. In `human-intervention-logs/com.oracle.database.jdbc:ojdbc11:23.8.0.25.04/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T08-37-18-679176Z.log`, `ShardingDriverExtensionTest > fallsBackToThinConnectionWhenTargetShardingKeyIsProvided()` is successful, and `tests/src/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows `oracle.jdbc.driver.ShardingDriverExtension.getConnection(ShardingDriverExtension.java:151)` covered, consistent with the reported `152/166` dynamic-access coverage. The run then fails because `RedirectorAnonymous3Test > redirectsAccessorValueThroughStaticValueOfMethod()` fails under native image with `ExceptionInInitializerError`, caused by `NoSuchMethodException` / `NoSuchMethodError` for `oracle.jdbc.driver.T2CStatement.<init>(T2CConnection, ResultSetType)`; the same failure is recorded in `tests/src/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`.\n\nThe final generation log confirms the last iteration was focused on the remaining `oracle.jdbc.driver.ShardingDriverExtension` `Class#newInstance()` site, so that target appears to have been solved before the native test failure blocked the run: `human-intervention-logs/com.oracle.database.jdbc:ojdbc11:23.8.0.25.04/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-04T08-35-42-876586Z.log`. Also note the preservation gap: `stats/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/execution-metrics.json` still reports `generated_loc: